Vesica Control Mesh v1.0

Circle-Halo Animation Layer

One-line definition

Triangles render the surface; circle-halos model relationships; vesicas encode interaction; animation expresses the relationship field.

⸻

1. Core Stack

Render Layer:      triangle mesh
Control Layer:     circle/sphere halos
Interaction Layer: vesica overlap zones
Behavior Layer:    deformation, smoothing, blending, texture flow
Meaning Layer:     trust, tension, alignment, bonding, separation

⸻

2. Primitive

Each triangle Tᵢ gets a halo:

Hᵢ = {
  center: cᵢ,
  radius: rᵢ,
  normal: nᵢ,
  velocity: vᵢ,
  stability: sᵢ,
  semantic_tag: optional
}

The triangle remains the GPU/render primitive.
The halo becomes the relationship primitive.

⸻

3. Vesica Interaction

For two halos Hᵢ and Hⱼ:

d = distance(cᵢ, cⱼ)

If:

d < rᵢ + rⱼ

then an interaction zone exists.

Vᵢⱼ = overlap(Hᵢ, Hⱼ)

That overlap is the vesica.

⸻

4. Influence Score

overlap_score(i,j) =
overlap_area(Hᵢ,Hⱼ) / min(area(Hᵢ), area(Hⱼ))

Then weight it by motion and orientation:

alignment(i,j) =
overlap_score
× normal_similarity(nᵢ,nⱼ)
× velocity_similarity(vᵢ,vⱼ)
× stability_score(i,j)

Final relationship weight:

wᵢⱼ = clamp(alignment(i,j), 0, 1)

⸻

5. Animation Update

Each triangle updates from its own motion plus neighbor influence:

motionᵢ =
own_motionᵢ + Σ wᵢⱼ · motionⱼ

Position update:

pᵢ(t+1) =
pᵢ(t) + motionᵢ · dt

Normal smoothing:

nᵢ(t+1) =
normalize(nᵢ + Σ wᵢⱼ · nⱼ)

Texture flow:

uvᵢ(t+1) =
uvᵢ(t) + Σ wᵢⱼ · flowⱼ · dt

⸻

6. Meaning Mapping

deep overlap     → harmony / bonding / compression
shallow overlap  → tension / distance / weak relation
no overlap       → separation / break
unstable overlap → conflict / flicker / shear
stable overlap   → trust / coherence / smooth flow

⸻

7. Pipeline

1. Build triangle mesh
2. Assign halo to each triangle or control cell
3. Detect halo overlaps
4. Compute vesica relationship weights
5. Apply smoothing/deformation through weights
6. Render final triangle mesh
7. Repeat every frame

⸻

8. Design Principle

Do not replace triangles. Elevate them.

Triangles answer:

What is the surface?

Vesicas answer:

What relationships are shaping the surface?

⸻

9. Canonical Pantheon Phrase

The triangle is the body.
The circle is the field.
The vesica is the handshake.
The animation is the relationship made visible.

⸻

10. Status

Classification: experimental animation-control grammar
Use case: organic deformation, symbolic motion, relationship-aware animation
Not claimed as: new rendering primitive or triangle replacement
Claimed as: higher-order control layer over triangle meshes